I have no conflict of interest to disclose. I removed content that appeared either promotional or subjective; removed information that seemed too technical; and cited recent articles published in news outlets to support the content of the article.

I removed the maintenance tags, as they were added without explanation, and it appears to me that the issue raised in the past regarding this article were addressed. Please correct me if I am wrong.
None of these are true, so I removed them

I removed the issues template--regarding "This article contains wording that promotes the subject in a subjective manner without imparting real information. (February 2018)" - this is plain false. "A major contributor to this article appears to have a close connection with its subject. (February 2018)" Even if this were true, there is nothing promotional about the article. "This article may contain wording that promotes the subject through exaggeration of unnoteworthy facts. (February 2018)" Again, the facts presented are all neutral. "The topic of this article may not meet Wikipedia's general notability guideline. (February 2018)" I was under the impression that all MD granting institutions in the United States were notable; I'm not sure on this one, though. "This article contains content that is written like an advertisement. (February 2018)" Again, as far as I can tell, everything in this article is non-promotional, and contains well sourced factual information.
